osr	SCO OpenServer
uw	SCO UnixWare
.TE
.SH ARCHITECTURE
.nf
src/
\(lq\(lq *.c              Core engine \(em parser, formatter,
\(bv                     process walker, file examiner
\(lq\(lq lib/             Shared library modules
\(ga\(lq dialects/        Per-OS kernel interface adapters
    \(lq\(lq linux/
    \(lq\(lq darwin/libproc/
    \(lq\(lq freebsd/
    \(lq\(lq n+obsd/
    \(lq\(lq n+os/
    \(lq\(lq sun/
    \(lq\(lq aix/
    \(lq\(lq du/
    \(lq\(lq hpux/pstat/
    \(lq\(lq osr/
    \(ga\(lq uw/
test/                Unit and integration test suites
bench/               Performance benchmarks
.fi
.PP
Each dialect provides three key headers \(em
.IR machine.h ,
.IR dlsof.h ,
.IR dproto.h
\(em that wire the core engine into the target OS kernel.
.SH PERFORMANCE
The core engine is tuned for speed where it matters:
.IP \(bu 2
.B "Compiler optimization:"
\-O2 on all targets.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "Lookup tables:"
character classification via precomputed
.IR explen[] ,
.IR printable[] ,
.IR cls[] ,
and
.IR hv[]
tables \(em up to 97x faster than per-character library calls.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "Binary search:"
PID and PGID selection lists are sorted at entry and searched via
O(log\ n) binary search \(em 2.4x faster at 100 entries, 10x at 1000.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "Manual formatting:"
field output and path construction bypass
.BR snprintf (3)
for 9\(en15x throughput.
.IP \(bu 2
.B "Hash tables:"
port cache, host cache, device lookup, and file name matching all use
power-of-2 hash tables with polynomial hashing.
.PP
Run
.B make bench
to see all 101 benchmarks on your hardware.
.SH TESTING
.B lsof
ships with a unit test suite and an integration test suite:
.PP
.RS
.B make check
.RE
.PP
This builds and executes
.B check_unit
(102 unit tests) and
.B check_integration
(13 integration tests), writing results to
.I check_unit.log
and
.I check_integration.log
in the build directory.
.SS Unit tests (test/test_unit.c)
Tests core algorithms in isolation \(em no kernel access or
lsof binary required:
.IP \(bu 2
Field ID constants \(em uniqueness, sequential indices, character mappings
.IP \(bu 2
.BR x2dev ()
\(em hex string to device number conversion
.IP \(bu 2
HASHPORT \(em port hash macro range, distribution, determinism
.IP \(bu 2
.BR safestrlen ()
\(em safe string length with unprintable character expansion
.IP \(bu 2
.BR compdev ()
\(em device table comparator, multi-key sort order
.IP \(bu 2
.BR comppid ()
\(em PID comparator, sorting, negative PIDs
.IP \(bu 2
.BR safepup ()
\(em unprintable character formatting
.IP \(bu 2
Flag constants \(em XO_* crossover flags, FSV_* file struct value flags
.IP \(bu 2
Memory safety \(em safe realloc patterns, leak detection
.SS Integration tests (test/test_integration.c)
Invokes the lsof binary and validates output:
.IP \(bu 2
Binary discovery and help/version flags
.IP \(bu 2
PID-based lookup and field output format (\-F)
.IP \(bu 2
Open file detection, CWD detection
.IP \(bu 2
TCP and UNIX socket detection
.IP \(bu 2
Invalid PID handling, AND selection (\-a), FD selection (\-d)
.SH BENCHMARKS
Measure performance of core operations:
.PP
.RS
.B make bench
.RE
.PP
This builds and runs
.BR benchmark_core ,
writing results to
.I benchmark_core.log
in the build directory.
101 benchmarks covering core operations, optimization comparisons, and
system call overhead.
.PP
.TS
l l.
Category	What it measures
_
x2dev	Hex parsing \(em short, prefixed, long strings
HASHPORT	Port hashing \(em full range and common ports
hashbyname	Name hashing \(em short names, paths, long paths
safestrlen	Safe string length \(em short, escaped, long paths
compdev sort	Device table sorting via qsort
safepup	Unprintable char formatting
safestrprt	Safe string printing
mkstrcat	String concatenation
I/O	open/close, stat, readdir, readlink, access, etc.
String ops	strlen, strcmp, strncmp, snprintf, isprint, strtol
Socket	TCP/UNIX socket create/close
Memory	malloc/free, realloc, memset/memcpy
Search	PID sort, binary search, field ID lookup
Matching	Regex match, strncmp prefix, FD status check
Path building	snprintf vs manual construction
Field output	snprintf vs manual lsof \-F formatting
.TE
.SS Optimization comparisons
Head-to-head comparisons measuring optimization impact.
Reference numbers from Apple M-series (single core):
.PP
.TS
l l l l.
Comparison	Before	After	Speedup
_
isprint() vs lookup table	11.1 ns/op	0.2 ns/op	55x
safestrlen: isprint vs explen[]	19.4 ns/op	0.2 ns/op	97x
Integer: snprintf vs manual	25.3 ns/op	1.7 ns/op	15x
PID scan (100): linear vs bsearch	23.1 ns/op	9.7 ns/op	2.4x
PID scan (1000): linear vs bsearch	189.8 ns/op	19.0 ns/op	10x
Regex vs strncmp	30.8 ns/op	1.7 ns/op	18x
Field output: snprintf vs manual	74.7 ns/op	4.9 ns/op	15x
Path building: snprintf vs manual	45.9 ns/op	4.9 ns/op	9x
.TE
.SH BUILDING FROM SOURCE
.SS CMake (recommended)
.RS
.nf
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make
sudo make install
.fi
.RE
.PP
Installs to
.I /usr/local/sbin/lsof
by default.
To change the prefix:
.PP
.RS
.B cmake \-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr ..
.RE
